review_blob: Pours hazy golden with a white head. Aroma of funk, barnyard and fruits. Taste is a bit tart. Good balance. Awesome complex of aromas and flavors.
Pours a hazy pale yellow with a huge white foamy head. Aroma of citrus, grassy, tropical fruits and a bit of spice. Taste is similar. Bitter finish. Kind of thin on the palate but still a good beer.
Pours golden with a medium off-white head. Aroma of pine, citrus & malt. Tastes of citrus, pine, resin, fruits, sweet & malt. Medium body. Good carbonation. Nice balance.
Pours dark brown with an off-white head. Aroma of malt, dark fruits and caramel. Tastes of roasted malt, spices, fruits & yeast. Well balanced. Good carbonation. Good drinkability.
Pours golden with a white diminishing head. Aroma is of yeast, citrus and alcohol. Tastes of malt, alcohol & yeast. Bitter finish.
Pours dark red with a good off-white head. Aroma of sugars and malts. Taste is very sweet. A very rich beer, full bodied. Mild carbonation.
Pours a murky copper-orange with a small off-white head. Aromas of citrus hops, lots of grapefruit and oranges. Tastes of juicy fresh hops-- delicious! Nice body, creamy mouthfeel.
Pours a clear and very pale yellow with a small white head. Mild aroma is grassy, grainy, a touch hoppy. Mild taste is similar to aroma with a bit of malt. Thin bodied.
Pours a dark reddish-brown with a small off-white head. Aromas of caramel malt and a bit smokey. Tastes of caramel malt, smoke, hops and alcohol. Medium bodied and smooth carbonation.
beer_name: Smuttynose Big Beer Series: Scotch Style Ale

review_blob: Pours a clear light gold with a small white head. Drinkable but nothing special to note.

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: Pours a hazy bubbly orange-yellow with a small white head. Nice lacing. Aromas of citrus hops, fruit, malt and spices. Tastes very juicy and citrusy -- quite refreshing. Medium bodied.

Pours a murky dark brown/black with a large creamy tan head. Aromas of earthy espresso and roasted malt. Tastes of sweet espresso with caramel malt, chocolate and a light hoppy finish. Thin to medium bodied with a creamy mouthfeel.
Pours black with a small light-brown head. Aromas of chocolate, nuts, roasted malt and dark fruit. Tastes of roasted malt, coffee, dark chocolate, fruit and a nice hoppy finish. Full bodied.
beer_name: Dark Horse Plead the 5th Imperial Stout

review_blob: Pours a hazy dark orange with a medium fluffy white head. Aromas of floral hops with a touch of spices. Tastes of juicy hops with enough malty sweetness-- delicious & refreshing. Nice and creamy, medium bodied.
Clear amber body with lots of small bubbles and a big foamy off-white head. Aromas of citrusy hops. Tastes of alcohol with some sweet fruit. Medium-full body.
Clear light yellow body with lots of bubbles and a quick bubbly white head. Grainy aromas. Taste is similar with a little sweet.

Pours a deep dark brown, almost black, with a large diminishing dark tan head. Aroma of roasted malt, chocolate and hops. Taste is just as good-- nice and roasty with malt, coffee, lots of chocolate and hops with a touch of alcohol. Great body. Easy to drink for an Imperial Stout.

Pours a clear amber-orange with a nice size lasting foamy off-white head. Aroma of caramel malt, fruit and mild hops. Mild but smooth flavour of caramel malt and alcohol with a light bitter finish. Light to medium bodied.

Pours a dark hazy red-brown with an average size off-white head. Sweet aroma of caramel malt, toffee, dark fruit and some roastiness. Taste is caramel malt, dark fruit, brown sugar, a touch of smoke and a light bitter finish. Alcohol shows up a little in the finish.
beer_name: Dark Horse Scotty Karate Scotch Ale

review_blob: Pours a clear, very bubbly, reddish-brown with a large lasting foamy off-white head. Mild aroma of caramel malt and a hint of roastiness. Watery flavour of caramel malt, nuts and a mild finish of roastiness and hops. Thin bodied with an almost creamy mouthfeel.

Poured a murky reddish-brown with a big long lasting foamy off-white head. Aroma of floral hops, sweet malt, some spices and a good amount of rye. Flavour of sweet malt, rye, spices, some alcohol and a long hoppy finish. Medium to full bodied.

Pours a cloudy amber with a small white head. Nice amount of carbonation. Aroma of fruity malts and hops with some citrus, plum and a whiff of alcohol. Flavour is quite bitter, a little strong on the alcohol but not too much. Nice balance of hops and sweet fruit and has a mild port or brandy taste. A little milder than some barley wines, its quite nice.
beer_name: Alley Kat Olde Deuteronomy Barley Wine

review_blob: Pours a hazy amber with a frothy average white head. Earthy aroma heavy on the hops with some citrus. Flavour wasnt as hoppy as I expected -- bitter, spicy and a bit malty. I found I could taste the alcohol a bit too much. May have been served a little too warm.

Appearance is a very dark brown with an average frothy off-white head. Good lacing. Aroma is pleasantly smoky with caramel malt and hops. Flavour is a lightly acidic combination of smoke, caramel malt, light hops and a touch of scotch that really works.

Beautiful black body with a light brown, creamy head. Great aroma of chocolate and coffee, spices, moderate hops and a bit of roasted malt. The flavour, which is pretty much perfect, consists of coffee, chocolate and all the other stuff I mentioned that was in the aroma. The palate is very smooth and creamy. An excellent stout.
Really nice beer. One of the better Ontario craft brews Ive had. Brownish amber in colour and aroma is of hop and spice. Taste as well is a nice palate of hop, spice and malt.
